		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">mic_ wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The second one was recorded while running on a CGB, but it's really a DMG demo.</div>
<br />Which wasn't a very good idea, some of the effects suffered because of the non-grayscale palette (the top of the mountains at the end are red!).
<br />
<br />Anyway, I think demos are a poor indication of a machine's power to run games. They are interesting for a while (although I usually find the music very repetitive), but non-interactive programs become uninteresting very quickly. I'm interested to know what these machines are capable of when running actual games.

		

